==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|semen||to seem, befit, be becoming}}, from {{etyl|non|en}} {{m|non|sœma||to conform to, beseem, befit}} (> Danish {{m|da|sømme||beseem}}) from {{m|non|sœmr||fitting, seemly}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*sōmijaną||to unite, fit}}, akin to Old Norse {{m|non|sómi|sōmi|honour}} ( > archaic Danish {{m|da|somme||decent comportment}}), {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|sēman||to reconcile, bring an agreement}}, Old English {{m|ang|sōm||agreement}}.

